value.value: An anatomical group whose component structures share a common function.

Cluster of two sets of sensilla in the larval labial segment, the labial organ and the ventral pharyngeal sense organ (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It is found in the atrium, with the labial sensory organ at the base and the labial organ on the lower lip of the external opening (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).
Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some larval head (FBbt:00001730).

Paired compound sense organ of the larval labral segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It consists of 6 sensilla in the dorsal larval pharynx: one tri-dendritic, 2 bi-dendritic and 3 mono-dendritic (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Projections generally, though not exclusively, target the contralateral subesophageal ganglion area 1 (Colomb et al., 2007).

definition.value: Colomb et al. (2007) report that labral nerve projections pass through area 2 and into area 1 of the subesophageal ganglion. In the majority of cases they then target the contralateral area 2. An exception to this is one DPS fiber (which labels with Gr2a-GAL4) which targets inside area 4.

Group of sense organs, and the somas and dendrites of sensory neurons, located ventrally in a larval segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It lies outside the ventrolateral and ventral muscles, beneath the ventral insertion of the lateral transverse muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It can be divided into two smaller clusters (ventral and ventral'), with the axons of neurons of each cluster following a different branch of the segmental nerve (Willams and Shepherd, 1999). The pattern of sense organs and neurons is highly similar in segments A1-7, and slightly modified in the thoracic segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

definition.value: Terminal (A8-10) segments have substantially different morphology, such that no 'ventral cluster' is present as seen in more anterior segments.

value.value: Cluster of sense organs, and the somas and dendrites of sensory neurons, located dorsally, close to the surface of a larval segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It lies above the dorsal insertion of the lateral transverse muscles, outside the dorsal intersegmental muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The pattern of sense organs and neurons is highly similar in segments A1-7, and slightly modified in the thoracic segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The axons of neurons in this cluster fasciculate with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

definition.value: Terminal (A8-10) segments have substantially different morphology, such that no 'dorsal cluster' is present as seen in more anterior segments.

value.value: Cluster of sense organs, and the somas and dendrites of sensory neurons, located laterally, close to the surface of a larval segment (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It is located in the niche formed between the lateral transverse muscles and the lateral epidermis (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The pattern of sense organs and neurons is highly similar in segments A1-7, and slightly modified in the thoracic segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The axons of most neurons in this cluster fasciculate with the intersegmental nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

definition.value: Terminal (A8-10) segments have substantially different morphology, such that no 'lateral cluster' is present as seen in more anterior segments.

Cell that forms the wall of the dorsal vessel. They are arranged in two medial rows connected by ventral and dorsal adhesion zones, leaving a central lumen (Medioni et al., 2008).

Cell that is part of the wall of the dorsal vessel of the late embryo or larva. It connects to a contralateral partner cardial cell dorsally and ventrally, via adhesive junctional domains, leaving a medial lumen (Medioni et al., 2008; Lehmacher et al., 2012). There are 104 of these cells per dorsal vessel (Lehmacher et al., 2012).

Embryonic precursor of a cardial cell, which forms part of the inner, contractile layer of the dorsal vessel. These cells become morphologically distinct during stage 14, when they stretch, flatten and develop dorsally directed processes (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). During dorsal closure, they are squeezed between the amnioserosa and epidermis, and the cardioblasts of either side meet at the dorsal midline once the amnioserosa separates from the epidermis (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). The dorsal vessel is formed when the lateral edges of the cardioblasts curve around ventrally to meet and interdigitate leaving a medial lumen (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). These cells do not finish differentiating into specialized subtypes until after larval hatching (Lehmacher et al., 2012).

Cardioblast which is a precursor of embryonic/larval heart cardial cell in the posterior dorsal vessel. During stage 14, these cells increase in size and elongate in the transverse axis to adopt a columnar shape.

Cardioblast which is the precursor of cardial cells of the aorta in the anterior dorsal vessel. These cells become distinct from heart cardioblasts during stage 14: they remain small and cuboidal while the heart cardioblasts enlarge and elongate to become columnar.

Embryonic cardioblast that will become a larval ostial cell (Molina and Cripps, 2001).They can be recognized by their expression of seven up, and in the assembled dorsal vessel of the late embryo, there are two in each of hemisegments A5-A7 (Molina and Cripps, 2001; Zaffran et al., 2006; Chen et al., 2016). They begin to differentiate into ostial cells at the end of embryogenesis (Lehmacher et al., 2012).
Any epithelial cell (FBbt:00000124) that is part of some epidermis (FBbt:00004993).

label.value: larval intersegmental nerve branch ISNb of A1-7

value.value: A ventral branch of the intersegmental nerve of segments A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve. Its branching point is dorsal to that of ISNd. It consists mostly of motorneuron axons whose soma is located in the next anterior segment, which innervate various ventral somatic muscles including muscles VO1-3 and VL1.

definition.value: ISNd could be considered a branch of ISNb, which is in turn a branch of ISN (Landgraf et al., 1997).

label.value: larval intersegmental nerve branch ISNd of A1-7

value.value: A ventral branch of the intersegmental nerve of segments A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the anterior root of the intersegmental nerve. Its branching point is ventral to that of ISNb. It consists mostly of motorneuron axons whose soma is located in the next anterior segment, which innervate various ventral somatic muscles.

definition.value: ISNd could be considered a branch of ISNb, which is in turn a branch of ISN (Landgraf et al., 1997).

label.value: larval segmental nerve branch SNa of A1-7

value.value: Dorsally directed branch of segmental nerve of larval A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the segmental nerve root. It innervates the external lateral transverse and oblique muscles and carries axons of sensillum vc5 (also known as vp5) and lch1.

label.value: larval segmental nerve branch SNc of A1-7

value.value: Posteriorly directed ventral branch of segmental nerve of larval A1-7 that exits the ventral nerve cord through the segmental nerve root. It innervates the external ventral acute musculature muscles and carries axons of the ventral sensory cluster.
